OpenDevScript By dudu.clx.

Based on great work from PSPdev, PS2dev, ps3dev and all his contributors.

__________________________________________________________________________
------> ps3devubuntu.sh
This script is to use on Linux Debian or Ubuntu.
Just run the script typing in the terminal:
sh ./ps3devubuntu.sh
and enter your password.

Will install psl1ght v2 and ps3tools into "/home/$USER/dev/ps3dev".
will install ps3keys into "/home/$USER/.ps3".

__________________________________________________________________________
------> ps3devmac.sh
This script is to use on Mac Osx (10.5 or higher).
You'll need to perform pre-install:
.Macports: https://www.macports.org/
.ActiveTCL 8.5 or higher: http://www.activestate.com/activetcl/downloads
.nvidia CG 3 (or higher): http://developer.nvidia.com/cg-toolkit
.Xcode 3.2.6 (and select ppc support): torrent client or anything else.
If xcode won't install, mount it and type in terminal:
    export COMMAND_LINE_INSTALL=1
    open "/Volumes/Xcode and iOS SDK/Xcode and iOS SDK.mpkg"

Just run the script typing in the terminal:
sh ./ps3devmac.sh

Will install psl1ght V2 and ps3tools into "/users/$USER/dev/ps3dev".
will install ps3keys into "/users/$USER/.ps3".

__________________________________________________________________________
------> ps2dev.sh
This script is to use on Linux Debian or Ubuntu.
Just run the script typing in the terminal:
sh ./ps2dev.sh
and enter your password.

Will install ps2sdk into "/home/$USER/dev/ps2dev".
Not all ps2sdk-ports will be installed.

__________________________________________________________________________
------> ps2opl.sh
This script will compile open-PS2-Loader and tools from ifcaro's sources.
"opl.elf" will be available in "/home/$USER/dev/ps2dev/open-ps2-loader".
"iso2opl" and "opl2iso" will be available in "/home/$USER/dev/ps2dev/open-ps2-loader/pc".

__________________________________________________________________________
------> pspdev.sh
This script is to use on Linux Debian or Ubuntu.
Just run the script typing in the terminal:
sh ./pspdev.sh
and enter your password.

Will install pspsdk into "/home/$USER/dev/pspdev".
None of psp-ports will be installed.